Por-Bajin was found in the centre of a lake in the mountains of southern Siberia . 
  The island was built during the Uighur Khaganate 1,300 years ago . 
  It is located 3,800km from Moscow near the Mongolian border . 
  Experts say it could have been a fortress or prison or a summer palace . 
  The location was first discovered in 1891 . 
 